Let me analyze both structures in the main target image and provide assembly instructions for each.

Left Structure (House with Arch):
- Has 3 layers
- Contains approximately 8-9 blocks
- Features a green base, red arch, orange roof pieces, and blue/green upper blocks

Right Structure (Abstract Building):
- Has 3 main layers
- Contains approximately 8 blocks
- Features blue pillars, yellow platform, and mixed colored upper sections

Let me provide the assembly instructions for both structures:

Left Structure (House with Arch):
{
    Step1: Move block with index 9 (green horizontal base)
    Step2: Move block with index 1 (red arch)
    Step3: Move block with index 6 (green cube left side)
    Step4: Move block with index 5 (blue cube right side)
    Step5: Move block with index 13 (orange slope left)
    Step6: Move block with index 14 (orange slope right)
}

Right Structure (Abstract Building):
{
    Step1: Move block with index 8 (blue vertical pillar left)
    Step2: Move block with index 8 (blue vertical pillar right)
    Step3: Move block with index 10 (yellow horizontal platform)
    Step4: Move block with index 7 (red cube right)
    Step5: Move block with index 5 (blue cube left)
    Step6: Move block with index 6 (green horizontal top)
    Step7: Move block with index 15 (orange slope left)
    Step8: Move block with index 16 (orange slope right)
}

Each structure uses blocks exactly as they appear in the dictionary without any rotation, and the assembly order follows a bottom-up approach for stability.
